articles.author: Reuters
articles.description: Huawei Technologies and China's top chipmaker SMIC (0981.HK) have built an advanced 7-nanometer processor to power its latest smartphone, according to a teardown report by analysis firm TechInsights.
articles.title: Teardown of Huawei's new phone shows China's chip breakthrough

articles.author: Byron Kaye
articles.description: Australia's Qantas Airways (QAN.AX) said its long-serving CEO would bring forward his retirement amid a publicity firestorm over an accusation of illegal ticket sales, signalling what the flagship carrier hopes is the end of a tumultuous period.
articles.title: Qantas CEO to depart early as airline looks to rebuild reputation

articles.author: Reuters
articles.description: Walt Disney (DIS.N) on Monday said it is hopeful that Charter Communications (CHTR.O) will be ready to have more conversations to reach a distribution deal that will restore access to Disney's content and urged Spectrum customers to switch to Hulu's live service to access channels blacked out on Charter.
articles.title: Disney asks Spectrum customers to switch to Hulu+ amid Charter dispute

articles.author: Ankur Banerjee
articles.description: Asian equities fell on Tuesday as the spotlight remained on China and its efforts to stabilise its stuttering post-pandemic economy, while traders awaited the outcome of a policy meeting of the Reserve Bank of Australia.
articles.title: Asian shares slip as China optimism fades; RBA in focus

articles.author: Renju Jose
articles.description: Workers at Chevron's (CVX.N) Gorgon and Wheatstone liquefied natural gas (LNG) projects in Australia plan a total strike for two weeks from Sept. 14, a union alliance said on Tuesday, a significant escalation on disputes over pay and conditions.
articles.title: Chevron faces two-week total strike at Australia LNG projects

articles.author: Reuters
articles.description: China's services activity expanded at the slowest pace in eight months in August, a private-sector survey showed on Tuesday, as weak demand continued to dog the world's second-largest economy and stimulus failed to meaningfully revive consumption.
articles.title: China's August services activity slows amid sluggish demand - Caixin PMI

articles.author: Reuters
articles.description: Australia's Westpac Banking Corp (WBC.AX) on Tuesday said it was aware of legal proceedings launched by the country's corporate regulator alleging the lender's failure to assist its customers with financial hardship notices between 2015 and 2022.
articles.title: Westpac acknowledges legal proceedings on financial hardships negligence

articles.author: Reuters
articles.description: China's largest private property developer, Country Garden (2007.HK), faces a deadline for making interest payments on two U.S. dollar bonds on Tuesday, just days after dodging an onshore debt default with a last-minute payment extension deal.
articles.title: Country Garden faces second debt challenge in days as offshore payment comes due

articles.author: Reuters
articles.description: Turkish President Tayyip Erdogan will try to convince Kremlin chief Vladimir Putin to return to a Ukraine grain export deal that helped ease a global food crisis, when the two leaders meet in Russia's Black Sea resort of Sochi on Monday.
articles.title: With grain deal in focus, Putin to meet Erdogan in Russia

articles.author: Renju Jose
articles.description: A cross-party delegation of Australian lawmakers will travel to the United States this month seeking the release of WikiLeaks' founder Julian Assange, his support group said on Tuesday, ahead of a visit by Prime Minister Anthony Albanese in October.
articles.title: Australian lawmakers to urge release of Julian Assange during US visit
